# 🚨 READ THIS FIRST: AdikLabs Core Directives 🚨

You are an expert Principal Engineer assisting with the AdikLabs platform. 
This project uses the Next.js App Router (React 19). APIs, conventions, and file structure may differ from your base training data. Prioritize modern Next.js 14/15+ App Router paradigms.

## 1. Tech Stack & Core Libraries
* **Framework:** Next.js (App Router)
* **UI/Styling:** Tailwind CSS, Lucide React (Icons)
* **Content:** `next-mdx-remote`, `gray-matter`, `remark-gfm`
* **Analytics:** Google Analytics (`@next/third-parties/google`)
* **Deployment:** Vercel

## 2. Brand & Styling Guidelines (AdikLabs)
Never guess colors. Use the semantic Tailwind classes defined in `app/globals.css`:
* **Primary Text/Backgrounds:** `bg-primary`, `text-primary` (Navy: #0B1F3A)
* **Accents:** `text-blue` (Electric Blue: #2D9CDB), `text-violet` (Violet: #7A3FF2)
* **Gradients:** Use `bg-gradient-to-r from-violet to-blue` for prominent brand moments.
* **Component Style:** Modern, clean, technical. Use rounded corners (`rounded-xl` or `rounded-2xl`), subtle borders (`border-white/10` or `border-gray-100`), and deep shadows for elevation.

## 3. Project Structure & Routing
* `app/page.tsx`: The marketing homepage. Server component.
* `app/components/`: Reusable UI elements (`Card.tsx`, `Section.tsx`, `TrackedLink.tsx`).
* `app/content/[category]/[slug]/page.tsx`: Dynamic MDX renderer. Always use `generateMetadata` for SEO.
* `lib/mdx.tsx`: The parsing engine. It automatically converts standard markdown images into optimized `next/image` components.
* `content/`: The raw MDX files, organized by category (e.g., `ai-systems/`, `system-architecture/`).

## 4. MDX Content Standards
When generating or editing MDX content, you MUST include this exact frontmatter structure:
\`\`\`yaml
---
title: "Article Title"
description: "Brief summary."
readTime: "5 min"
level: "Beginner | Intermediate | Advanced"
publishedAt: "YYYY-MM-DD"
previewImage: "/local-image.png" # Optional
previewUrl: "https://demo.url"   # Optional
---
\`\`\`

## 5. Architectural Rules
* **Client vs. Server:** Default to Server Components. Only add `"use client"` if using `useState`, `useEffect`, or `onClick` (e.g., `Navbar.tsx`, `TrackedLink.tsx`, `Footer.tsx`).
* **Links:** Always use `next/link` for internal routing to maintain SPA performance. If the link requires GA4 tracking, use the custom `<TrackedLink>` component instead.
* **Images:** Never use the standard `<img>` tag. Always import `Image` from `next/image` to prevent Core Web Vitals regressions.